WEBVTT

00:02.083 --> 00:03.583
Erica: (Giggling)

00:03.625 --> 00:05.000
Man: The best part was...
Erica: Uh-huh.

00:05.041 --> 00:06.917
Man: When she said,
"um, aren't those my pants"?

00:06.959 --> 00:08.875
Both: (Giggle)

00:08.917 --> 00:10.500
- You know what, Mike?

00:10.542 --> 00:12.959
I haven't had this much fun
in a really long time.

00:13.000 --> 00:15.083
(Cell phone ringing)
Gotta say.

00:17.041 --> 00:19.250
Oh, would you excuse me,
just for a second?
I have to take this.

00:19.291 --> 00:21.166
- Yeah, no worries.
- Thank you.

00:22.792 --> 00:26.375
- (Whispers) Ethan.
- This is a test of the
emergency broadcast system.

00:26.417 --> 00:28.458
- I don't think I need it.
I think it's going really well.

00:29.625 --> 00:31.083
- I hear a "but" coming.

00:31.125 --> 00:33.417
- No, no "buts".
I mean... he seems nice,

00:33.458 --> 00:35.458
and he's... he's cute
and... smart and funny.

00:38.083 --> 00:40.208
- But?

00:40.250 --> 00:43.041
- Where's the catch?
- Here's a thought.
Maybe there isn't one.

00:43.083 --> 00:45.125
Just leave it at that,
enjoy yourself.

00:45.166 --> 00:47.208
- I will. I am, totally.

00:47.250 --> 00:49.500
Only call if Godzilla attacks.

00:49.542 --> 00:50.834
(Cell phone beeps off)

00:52.375 --> 00:53.750
- So what should we do now?

00:55.208 --> 00:56.917
- Uh, well...

00:58.542 --> 01:00.041
It's getting pretty late.
Everything's closing.

01:01.625 --> 01:03.125
- Yeah.
- But, uh I do live right there.

01:05.333 --> 01:06.834
- Really?

01:08.333 --> 01:09.875
One drink?
- Yeah.

01:09.917 --> 01:11.291
- Okay.

01:14.709 --> 01:16.917
Okay, it's official,
I need to move in here.

01:18.542 --> 01:20.375
Not... Not...
I mean, into the building,

01:20.417 --> 01:23.166
not your actual apartment.
(Chuckles awkwardly)

01:23.208 --> 01:25.500
(To self) On our first date,
Erica. (Clears throat)

01:29.458 --> 01:30.834
Oh.

01:32.375 --> 01:33.792
- Oh, yeah. Sorry about that.

01:33.834 --> 01:35.792
I'm a secret slob
when it comes to dishes.

01:35.834 --> 01:38.166
- Oh, thank you.

01:40.417 --> 01:42.333
Oh, Mike, these are amazing.

01:42.375 --> 01:45.041
- I love African masks.

01:45.083 --> 01:47.667
Spent six months in Kenya
last year.

01:47.709 --> 01:49.834
That one there, that was carved
from a Mpingo tree.

01:52.291 --> 01:53.875
- May I?
- Sure.

01:56.625 --> 01:58.458
(Exhales in awe)

02:02.291 --> 02:04.291
- Wow.

02:04.333 --> 02:06.250
Mpingo... It's very Kenyan.

02:10.291 --> 02:11.875
(Gulping)

02:15.208 --> 02:17.000
- So, do you want another drink?

02:17.041 --> 02:18.875
- Yes, thank you. I sure do.

02:20.500 --> 02:22.500
The first date is like
an open house.

02:22.542 --> 02:25.208
The pictures look great,
the dimensions are good,

02:25.250 --> 02:27.583
and as you stand
on the threshold, you think,

02:27.625 --> 02:29.417
could this be it?
Could this be the one?

02:35.750 --> 02:37.500
Um, do you mind
if we just... okay.

02:40.291 --> 02:42.083
You open the door
full of anticipation,

02:43.542 --> 02:45.041
you walk in,

02:45.083 --> 02:47.291
and then you start to notice
the details:

02:47.333 --> 02:49.500
the cracks in the wall,
the weird little quirks.

02:49.542 --> 02:51.583
And then you think, no...

02:53.375 --> 02:54.875
this isn't for me.

02:56.333 --> 02:58.000
Um, Mike,

02:58.041 --> 02:59.542
you know, I think that
I should, uh...

02:59.583 --> 03:01.542
I should probably
just get going now, so...

03:03.959 --> 03:05.375
- Oh. I can drive you.

03:05.417 --> 03:06.834
- No, that's okay. Uh, the cab,

03:06.875 --> 03:08.208
I'm just gonna,
I'm gonna call a cab.

03:08.250 --> 03:10.500
But thank you.
Thanks for the night.

03:12.041 --> 03:13.333
(Door opens and shuts)

03:14.792 --> 03:24.208
♪ ♪

03:24.250 --> 03:27.000
♪ It's clearer inside of me ♪

03:27.041 --> 03:29.458
♪ Who I will always be ♪

03:29.500 --> 03:32.375
♪ Open me up to my heart ♪

03:34.500 --> 03:37.125
♪ Feels like I'm seeing
in the dark ♪

03:37.166 --> 03:39.417
♪ Waking me up to my heart ♪

03:39.458 --> 03:41.458
♪ To do it all over ♪

03:41.500 --> 03:44.333
♪ Again and again ♪

03:44.375 --> 03:47.000
♪ Until the end ♪

03:47.041 --> 03:49.458
♪ The sum of my dreams ♪

03:49.500 --> 03:52.291
♪ And everything
I ever wanted to be ♪

03:57.417 --> 04:00.542
Erica: Bring it.
Ethan: (Grunts) African masks,
can't have that.

04:00.583 --> 04:02.875
- It was made in Taiwan.
He said he bought it in Africa.

04:02.917 --> 04:05.000
I mean, does he not check
the labels?

04:06.667 --> 04:08.333
- You know, you always do this.
You're like a bloodhound.

04:08.375 --> 04:10.333
- You sniff out the weirdest
things about these guys.

04:10.375 --> 04:12.542
- How do I even know
that he's been to Africa?

04:12.583 --> 04:14.917
Maybe the masks are like a prop
to get girls to think that
he's cultured.

04:16.458 --> 04:17.834
- Or maybe you're the weird one.

04:17.875 --> 04:19.500
- Oh, oh, and did I tell you

04:19.542 --> 04:21.250
about the Idiot's Guide
to Dostoevsky?

04:22.792 --> 04:24.125
- Yes! Advantage, Federer.

04:25.667 --> 04:26.959
You never read Doestoevsky.

04:27.000 --> 04:29.125
- I loved Anna Karenina.

04:29.166 --> 04:31.000
- Erica, that's Tolstoy.

04:31.041 --> 04:32.667
- All I'm saying is that
why can't I meet somebody

04:32.709 --> 04:34.875
who's not damaged or crazy or...

04:34.917 --> 04:36.583
or a fake African mask
collector.

04:36.625 --> 04:38.291
I mean, what is wrong with me?

04:39.792 --> 04:41.291
- You suck at Wii?

04:42.750 --> 04:44.750
- That's funny.

04:44.792 --> 04:47.208
No, you're great,
it's the process that sucks.

04:47.250 --> 04:48.917
Being single, dating,

04:48.959 --> 04:51.417
wanting something
you can't find or can't keep.

04:51.458 --> 04:53.667
It's endless.
- Mm-hmm.

04:53.709 --> 04:56.583
- Ooh...

04:56.625 --> 04:58.458
You want to find a patio
and get wasted?

04:58.500 --> 05:01.834
- Absolutely. But I can't.
I have to uh...

05:01.875 --> 05:03.792
go help Judith decorate
the high school gym,

05:03.834 --> 05:05.750
and I'm gonna be late.

05:05.792 --> 05:08.125
- Mm! Oh, the big reunion.
You psyched?

05:08.166 --> 05:10.041
- Not exactly.
- Why not?

05:10.083 --> 05:12.542
- Um, you know why.

05:12.583 --> 05:14.458
I mean, come on,
I'm-I'm single and unemployed.

05:16.041 --> 05:17.542
Not exactly a raging success.

05:17.583 --> 05:19.250
You know the thing about people
that peak in high school?

05:19.291 --> 05:21.375
That might be me.

05:21.417 --> 05:23.333
- No, it's not.

05:24.875 --> 05:26.417
- Okay, then I guess
I'm just a paranoid freak.

05:27.917 --> 05:29.792
Look, I'll call you later.

05:29.834 --> 05:31.250
Best of three.

05:31.291 --> 05:33.208
- All right. Have fun.

05:34.875 --> 05:36.875
Erica: So, Jessica Robertson
and Becky Blok emailed

05:36.917 --> 05:38.709
to say that they're gonna
make it.

05:38.750 --> 05:40.458
Judith: I never liked Jessica.

05:40.500 --> 05:41.750
Ever since she played Juliet
in grade twelve,

05:41.792 --> 05:43.333
that went straight to her head.

05:43.375 --> 05:45.250
- Wow, you hold a grudge.

05:45.291 --> 05:47.333
- (Laughs) You should talk.

05:49.417 --> 05:51.083
Okay. Don't be mad.
- What?

05:52.625 --> 05:54.041
- I forgot to tell you...

05:54.083 --> 05:56.625
Katie's coming in
from Vancouver for this.

05:56.667 --> 05:58.500
- You "forgot" to tell me?
Katie: Erica!

06:00.041 --> 06:01.417
- (Fake excited squeal)
- How are you?

06:02.959 --> 06:04.417
Oh. It is so great to see you.

06:04.458 --> 06:05.750
- Uh, how are things?

06:07.375 --> 06:09.417
- Just switched jobs.
Okay, it was a promotion.

06:09.458 --> 06:11.417
(Chuckles) I have my own column
at The Globe now.

06:11.458 --> 06:13.000
Vancouver office.

06:13.041 --> 06:15.375
- Oh, wow, congratulations.
That's great.

06:15.417 --> 06:17.208
- My bosses are billing me
as the new Leah Mclaren.

06:18.834 --> 06:21.000
I promised them something
about the reunion.

06:21.041 --> 06:22.834
You know, who was the least
likely to succeed, but did.

06:22.875 --> 06:24.583
Who was most likely to succeed

06:24.625 --> 06:27.458
but instead, peaked in high
school.

06:29.875 --> 06:31.500
How about you guys? Erica,
what're you doing these days?

06:31.542 --> 06:33.375
- Um, actually, I'm just
between jobs right now.

06:34.959 --> 06:36.667
- Re-evaluating, huh?
Good for you!

06:38.291 --> 06:39.834
You can get so caught up
in a career,

06:39.875 --> 06:41.583
the fast track...

06:41.625 --> 06:43.041
And how's Anthony doing?

06:43.083 --> 06:44.917
- He's great.
- Awesome.

06:44.959 --> 06:47.834
He is such a nice guy.

06:47.875 --> 06:49.166
But sometimes even
with the nice ones,

06:49.208 --> 06:50.792
you just want to smack 'em.

06:50.834 --> 06:53.500
Both: (Polite laughter)
- I remember before
I married Brian,

06:53.542 --> 06:55.417
all that time,
all those options.

06:57.000 --> 06:58.291
Tomorrow night
is the perfect night

06:58.333 --> 06:59.875
for you to be single, Erica.

06:59.917 --> 07:01.917
You are gonna have your pick
of all your old flames -

07:01.959 --> 07:03.959
the ones that aren't gay
or married yet.

07:04.000 --> 07:05.917
- Actually, Katie,
I am seeing someone

07:05.959 --> 07:07.792
and uh... he's amazing.

07:07.834 --> 07:09.750
We're actually,
we're quite serious.

07:11.625 --> 07:13.750
- Really? Well, I can't wait
to meet him tomorrow night.

07:16.625 --> 07:18.750
Do you know who will be there?
Zach Creed.

07:18.792 --> 07:20.583
He's the reunion photographer.
Ironic, huh?

07:22.125 --> 07:23.875
- I forgot to tell you that,
too.

07:26.333 --> 07:28.208
- What do you care?
You got your guy.

07:28.250 --> 07:29.667
It's all water under the bridge.

07:29.709 --> 07:31.333
- Mm, yeah. Ha.

07:31.375 --> 07:33.417
Anyway, I should go
get my ticket.

07:33.458 --> 07:35.917
I'll see you ladies
tomorrow night.

07:35.959 --> 07:37.875
- Heh.
- Ciao, ciao! (Titters)

07:41.750 --> 07:44.542
- What the hell are you doing?
- (Sighs) I don't know.

07:44.583 --> 07:46.834
Ethan: Why would you tell Katie
you have a boyfriend?

07:46.875 --> 07:48.750
- I don't know!
I can't stand that woman!

07:48.792 --> 07:51.417
She just, she automatically
assumed that I was single

07:51.458 --> 07:54.375
and that was it. It was like
the last straw and...

07:54.417 --> 07:56.333
So now I have to bring
this imaginary boyfriend
to the reunion

07:56.375 --> 07:57.792
and I'm so screwed.

07:57.834 --> 07:59.458
- (Laughing) You are just like--

07:59.500 --> 08:02.291
- Yeah, a moron. Thank you.
Thank you for that.

08:02.333 --> 08:04.417
So, will you do it?
- What?!

08:04.458 --> 08:05.917
- Please Ethan, be my boyfriend.

08:05.959 --> 08:08.375
You can do it.
I mean, you're smart

08:08.417 --> 08:10.792
and you're charming,
and you're funny and...

08:10.834 --> 08:12.792
- And I could use a night off
from thinking about my divorce.

08:12.834 --> 08:14.625
- Yes!

08:14.667 --> 08:16.041
- I'll be Sven,
the Swedish diplomat.

08:16.083 --> 08:18.500
- No.
- Jorge, the museum curator?

08:18.542 --> 08:21.417
- No, listen. Katie will
recognize you From U of T.

08:21.458 --> 08:24.250
You just gotta be you,
the best you that you can be.

08:24.291 --> 08:26.750
- What, soon-to-be divorced
elementary school teacher
not good enough for you?

08:26.792 --> 08:28.625
- No. You know what I'm saying.

08:30.166 --> 08:31.792
Oh, okay, this is my interview.

08:31.834 --> 08:34.333
Can you do me a favor?
Can you call Jenny and Judith

08:34.375 --> 08:35.834
and make sure they know
the plan?

08:35.875 --> 08:37.500
And make sure Jenny knows
to keep her mouth shut.

08:39.083 --> 08:41.500
- Got it. (Light kiss)
Good luck.

08:41.542 --> 08:42.875
- Thank you.

08:44.875 --> 08:46.667
Ambrose: Name some of your
favorite books.

08:46.709 --> 08:48.667
Erica: Favorite books? Wow.

08:48.709 --> 08:50.625
"1984."

08:50.667 --> 08:53.625
"A Handmaid's Tale."
"Of Human Bondage."

08:53.667 --> 08:55.000
"Franny and Zooey."

08:55.041 --> 08:57.291
- Uh, all fiction.

08:57.333 --> 08:59.000
- Yeah, I'm a fiction lover.

08:59.041 --> 09:00.959
- Applying for a job
in a non-fiction department.

09:02.583 --> 09:03.959
- (Awkward laugh)

09:07.792 --> 09:09.917
- So... tell me about
what you want to do.

09:12.667 --> 09:14.166
- Well, to be honest, I'm...

09:14.208 --> 09:16.875
I'm fascinated by the process
of taking an idea

09:16.917 --> 09:19.125
and shaping it into
a manuscript.

09:19.166 --> 09:21.458
I, I don't have a lot
of publishing experience,

09:21.500 --> 09:23.959
but I am a critical thinker and
I'm really motivated to learn.

09:25.667 --> 09:27.709
- You're far better spoken
than the 21-year-old grads

09:27.750 --> 09:29.792
I normally interview
for this job.

09:29.834 --> 09:31.792
But, I'll be honest,

09:31.834 --> 09:34.959
I've never considered
hiring someone as...

09:35.000 --> 09:38.625
well, mature as yourself
for a position like this.

09:38.667 --> 09:41.542
I just want to make sure that
you realize that this job is--

09:41.583 --> 09:44.125
- A hundred percent clerical?
Sorry to cut you off.

09:44.166 --> 09:47.041
- (Laughing) That's okay.
Yes, it's, uh...

09:47.083 --> 09:49.709
An assistant job. Entry level.

09:49.750 --> 09:52.208
- Absolutely. And I would be
expecting to make coffee

09:52.250 --> 09:54.917
and photocopy and collate
until my fingers grow calluses,

09:54.959 --> 09:56.959
and just... um...
- (Chuckling)

09:58.583 --> 10:00.458
Well, thank you for coming in.

10:02.083 --> 10:03.917
I'll make my decision
in the next few days.

10:03.959 --> 10:06.000
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

10:06.041 --> 10:08.000
- Lovely to meet you.
- Yes.

10:09.750 --> 10:11.041
Erica: Do I have anything
in my teeth?

10:11.083 --> 10:12.542
- Big chunk of spinach.

10:12.583 --> 10:14.000
- Shut- (laughing)
- (Laughing)

10:14.041 --> 10:15.375
- Okay. We're holding hands,
we're walking in.

10:16.875 --> 10:18.333
Oh, crap. Wait.
- What?

10:18.375 --> 10:19.583
- 'Kay, there's Katie.
She's right there.

10:22.041 --> 10:23.709
- Cue the devastating charm.

10:23.750 --> 10:26.625
- No! 'Kay, we need an exit
strategy

10:26.667 --> 10:28.083
in case things
start to go wrong.

10:28.125 --> 10:29.750
Speaking of which,
did you tell Jenny and Judith?

10:29.792 --> 10:31.583
- Check. They have been
informed.
- Okay.

10:33.875 --> 10:35.709
- Let's do it, all right.
- Let's go.
- All right.

10:35.750 --> 10:37.792
♪ Life can deal a hand
so mean ♪

10:39.291 --> 10:41.375
♪ I was only seventeen ♪

10:44.333 --> 10:46.750
Erica: Okay, this is the plan:
we approach her, introductions,

10:46.792 --> 10:48.959
get this over with
so we can relax.

10:49.000 --> 10:51.458
Hey, you see me flip
my hair like this,

10:51.500 --> 10:53.083
that means abort the mission.

10:54.959 --> 10:56.917
- Smile! (Camera clicks)
Hey, Erica!

10:56.959 --> 10:58.875
Long time no see.

10:58.917 --> 11:02.000
- Hi, Zach. This is Ethan.
- Hey, man, Zach Creed.

11:02.041 --> 11:04.125
Oh, you two mind posing
for a few?

11:04.166 --> 11:06.208
I'm getting shots for
the "then and now" photo tree.

11:06.250 --> 11:08.583
- No thanks.
- Sure.

11:08.625 --> 11:10.291
Come on, it'll be fun.

11:10.333 --> 11:12.959
Come on, Erica,
let's see that smile.

11:13.000 --> 11:15.083
I know you know how to "move."

11:15.125 --> 11:16.917
Come on, let's see that smile,
Erica.

11:16.959 --> 11:18.500
(Camera clicks)

11:18.542 --> 11:21.000
- Ethan! Ethan, don't.
- That's it, Erica!

11:21.041 --> 11:22.667
Smile for the camera.
(Creepy chuckle)

11:24.166 --> 11:25.458
(Camera shutter clicks)

11:30.041 --> 11:32.125
- Can you just put me down
for a second?
- What's the matter?

11:32.166 --> 11:33.709
Nothing. Um, I just,

11:33.750 --> 11:35.875
I have to go use the restroom
for a second.

11:35.917 --> 11:38.166
- Okay.
- I'll be back.

11:38.208 --> 11:40.583
♪ Life can deal a hand
so mean ♪

11:40.625 --> 11:42.792
♪ I was only seventeen ♪
(Camera clicks)

11:45.458 --> 11:47.542
♪ Everything was all mixed up
and I started to change ♪

11:51.709 --> 11:55.166
♪ Questions filled
my angry head ♪

11:55.208 --> 11:57.709
♪ Looking for an answer
from you... ♪

12:02.959 --> 12:05.041
- (Calming breaths)
Okay...

12:07.208 --> 12:09.709
(Heavy exhale)

12:09.750 --> 12:11.917
- You look like you just
knocked over the Bunsen burner.

12:14.542 --> 12:16.959
- Alex Berlin?

12:17.000 --> 12:18.709
Oh my God.

12:18.750 --> 12:21.000
You look so different.

12:21.041 --> 12:22.750
- No goggles. No lab coat.

12:24.250 --> 12:25.709
You look the same.

12:25.750 --> 12:27.625
Minus the ponytail, you know.
- Yes.

12:27.667 --> 12:30.166
I remember the scrunchies.
Huge collection.

12:30.208 --> 12:32.208
- (Chuckles) Wow.
This is really weird.

12:32.250 --> 12:34.333
I think that you just said
more to me in the last minute,

12:34.375 --> 12:36.709
than you did the entire year
we were lab partners.

12:36.750 --> 12:38.583
- That's probably true.
I was horribly shy.

12:40.250 --> 12:41.959
- Well, clearly not anymore.
(Speechless stammer)

12:43.500 --> 12:45.083
- Yeah.
- Wow. (Chuckles)

12:47.834 --> 12:49.166
Ah...

12:50.834 --> 12:52.542
- Well, it was great
seeing you again, Erica.

12:54.041 --> 12:55.500
- You too, really.

12:57.166 --> 12:59.000
- You look great.
- You too.

12:59.041 --> 13:00.875
- Thank you.

13:00.917 --> 13:03.542
- See you inside?
- Mm-hmm!

13:03.583 --> 13:06.083
I'll see you in there.

13:06.125 --> 13:07.959
(Muted beat of dance music)

13:09.500 --> 13:11.875
- Ethan, where do you live now?

13:11.917 --> 13:13.959
- You know, I-I-I'm...
I'm still working that out.

13:14.000 --> 13:16.083
Katie: Erica!

13:16.125 --> 13:17.792
So, Ethan is the mystery man.

13:19.333 --> 13:21.750
Old friends in love. So sweet!

13:21.792 --> 13:24.250
- Yeah, well, it took us a while
to finally come to our senses.

13:24.291 --> 13:26.083
- Hey, if you're looking for
a little action on the side,

13:26.125 --> 13:28.041
I'm available.
- Jenny!

13:28.083 --> 13:29.959
- Sorry, I can't help myself.
Your man looks smokin' hot.

13:31.792 --> 13:34.208
- So tell me,
what do you do now?

13:34.250 --> 13:37.000
- Actually, I'm... I'm a doctor.

13:37.041 --> 13:39.250
- A doctor! Really?
That, that's so interesting

13:39.291 --> 13:42.041
because I did a piece on
the medical profession
earlier this year.

13:42.083 --> 13:43.834
Let me, let me just
steal him away.

13:43.875 --> 13:46.250
So what is your specialty?

13:46.291 --> 13:48.083
(Low hum of chatter,
dance music plays)

13:52.917 --> 13:55.000
