33:05.792 --> 33:09.041
She... she had my number.

33:09.083 --> 33:11.917
The only girl to see through me
that way.

33:11.959 --> 33:14.375
But you guys look good together.

33:14.417 --> 33:16.375
A girl like that, man,
you do not just walk away from.

33:19.125 --> 33:22.166
I hope you had a good reason.

33:22.208 --> 33:24.125
- It's what she wants.

33:26.500 --> 33:28.291
(Muted beat of dance music)

33:30.458 --> 33:32.125
- (Laughing)

33:32.166 --> 33:34.000
And when you pushed him
into the water,

33:34.041 --> 33:36.041
I swear to God, I thought that
he was gonna come out of that
lake and--

33:36.083 --> 33:38.583
- Eat me for lunch?
- Yes.

33:38.625 --> 33:41.041
- My one moment of bravery.
It was so unlike me.

33:43.583 --> 33:46.208
I remember...
reading you that poem.

33:46.250 --> 33:48.792
- Mm-hmm.
- And thinking...

33:48.834 --> 33:51.166
How am I doing this?

33:51.208 --> 33:53.166
How is it possible for...

33:53.208 --> 33:55.291
this girl to make me feel
like I can do anything?

33:59.542 --> 34:02.458
- Okay, well, enough about
the past,

34:02.500 --> 34:04.583
what are you up to these days?

34:04.625 --> 34:06.417
- Well, um, my life's been
pretty busy, actually.

34:06.458 --> 34:08.125
I work the railroads.

34:08.166 --> 34:10.041
- Ooh! How very Jack Kerouac
of you.

34:11.667 --> 34:13.125
