a lot of writing.

34:13.166 --> 34:15.291
- Uh, no-no-no, I mean,
I actually work for a railroad.

34:15.333 --> 34:17.166
In logistics.
- Oh.

34:17.208 --> 34:18.625
- Yeah-yeah-yeah.
- Oh, okay.

34:18.667 --> 34:20.208
- Yeah, over the past
couple years,

34:20.250 --> 34:22.291
I've really developed
a passion for trains.

34:22.333 --> 34:23.959
- Really?

34:24.000 --> 34:26.625
Um, so like the aesthetics or--

34:26.667 --> 34:29.542
- All of it. Just the
engineering, the-the look.

34:29.583 --> 34:32.458
I collect train sets. Have you
ever heard of the Maglev?

34:32.500 --> 34:35.375
- Uh... no.
- It's this really cool
levitating train.

34:35.417 --> 34:36.792
It's the fastest in the world.

34:36.834 --> 34:38.417
It's comparable
to a jet aircraft.

34:38.458 --> 34:39.750
- Really?
- Yeah.

34:39.792 --> 34:41.166
- Hmm. Wow.

34:41.208 --> 34:43.792
(Dance music plays)

34:48.291 --> 34:51.500
- I remember when you drew on
Andrew Reubenfair's penis
with a highlighter

34:51.542 --> 34:54.750
on a field trip
to the science center!

34:54.792 --> 34:57.250
- I remember when you asked
if you could get a tan

34:57.291 --> 35:00.583
sitting by the fire
at Marni Moscow's cottage!

35:00.625 --> 35:03.417
- I remember when you
used to bark back at dogs

35:03.458 --> 35:05.333
on the way to school!
(Laughing)

35:05.375 --> 35:08.083
Ruff, ruff, ruff.
- Ruff!

35:08.125 --> 35:10.709
All: (Laughing and barking)

35:10.750 --> 35:12.625
- Oh my God, I haven't laughed
this hard since high school.

35:12.667 --> 35:15.125
- I know, I know.
- (Laughing)

35:15.166 --> 35:17.000
- Where's Erica?
- I don't know!

35:17.041 --> 35:20.208
She's all gaga over Alex Berlin.

35:20.250 --> 35:23.000
- Alex Berlin?
I thought she was with Ethan?

35:24.542 --> 35:26.875
- Oh, sh... Shit.

35:28.500 --> 35:31.041
- I knew it.
- No, K-Katie, don't say
anything.

35:34.000 --> 35:35.834
- It's called electro-dynamic
suspension,

35:35.875 --> 35:37.375
or E.D.S.

35:37.417 --> 35:39.208
You see, the rail exerts
a magnetic field,

35:39.250 --> 35:41.166
and the train exerts one back.

35:41.208 --> 35:42.667
Like when you have two magnets
with the same polarity

35:42.709 --> 35:44.417
and you just can't
get them to stick.

35:44.458 --> 35:47.000
- Mmm.
Katie: Erica!

35:47.041 --> 35:50.166
- Oh. Uh, hi.
Uh... Katie, this is...

35:50.208 --> 35:52.417
Do you remember Alex Berlin?

35:52.458 --> 35:54.166
I just wanted to come over
and tell you

35:54.208 --> 35:56.291
I so enjoyed re-connecting

35:56.333 --> 35:59.709
with your very accomplished
boyfriend.

35:59.750 --> 36:02.291
Did he do his medical degree
at Harvard or Columbia?

36:02.333 --> 36:05.667
'Cause I just can't remember
which one it was.

36:05.709 --> 36:08.375
I gotta say, I'm really
surprised.

36:08.417 --> 36:10.333
Making up a fake boyfriend?

36:12.333 --> 36:15.041
That's a new low,
even for you.

36:15.083 --> 36:16.834
Excuse me.

36:18.375 --> 36:20.417
- Alex.

36:20.458 --> 36:22.750
Alex, this isn't- I mean,
it isn't what it looks like.

36:22.792 --> 36:25.041
Yes, I did make up
a fake boyfriend and...

36:27.709 --> 36:29.750
the reasons why I did it,
they're really complicated.

36:29.792 --> 36:31.291
And I just, I really hope
that you can understand--

36:31.333 --> 36:32.542
- You don't owe me
an explanation.

36:32.583 --> 36:34.125
We barely know each other,
right?

36:36.291 --> 36:38.333
Whatever's going on
between you and this guy--

36:38.375 --> 36:40.125
- No, there's nothing--
nothing's going on. There's--

36:40.166 --> 36:42.542
- Look, I just got out
of a long relationship

36:42.583 --> 36:44.542
with a woman who cheated on me.

36:46.166 --> 36:49.000
I just can't deal with baggage
right now.

36:50.583 --> 36:52.375
See you around.

36:59.458 --> 37:00.792
(Sighs heavily)

37:02.291 --> 37:03.625
